the 1990 elections are a dream come true for 
political handicappers there are 34 senate races 36 governors 
contests and 435 us house contests on tuesdays ballot 
here is the outlook for the closest races according to a 
statebystate survey by the associated press 
alabama gov guy hunt the first republican elected governor 
in the state this century is bidding for a second term and 
narrowly leads democrat paul hubbert 
alaska as a republican walter hickel was alaskas second 
governor now hes back running as an independent and leading 
republican arliss sturgulewski and democrat tony knowles 
democratic incumbent steve cowper is not running 
arizona former phoenix mayor terry goddard a democrat leads 
gop developer fife symington but polls have him below the 50 
percent he needs to avoid a runoff incumbent rose mofford a 
democrat is retiring 
california the big race of 1990 is a megabuck contest for 
governor between republican sen pete wilson and former san 
francisco mayor dianne feinstein a lot of polling with not much 
agreement but the latest surveys give a hairline edge to wilson 
the result might have to await a count of absentee ballots days 
after the polls close 
connecticut republican lowell weicker lost his senate seat in 
1988 now hes running for governor as an independent and leading 
republican john rowland and democrat bruce morrison 
florida another highstakes contest for governor republican 
bob martinez was at the top of the democrats list of vulnerable 
incumbents democrats got another boost when former sen lawton 
chiles decided to challenge martinez late polls said chiles was 
leading but its close 
hawaii this usually democratic state gives the republicans 
their best shot at picking up a senate seat rep pat saiki is 
running a strong race against sen daniel akaka who was appointed 
to succeed the late sen spark matsunaga polls indicate the race 
is a tossup 
idaho republican sen james mcclure is retiring and rep larry 
craig is favored to defeat democrat ron twilegar in the senate 
race 
illinois republican jim edgar and democrat neil hartigan are 
running neck and neck to succeed gop gov jim thompson in the 
senate race democrat paul simon holds a wide lead over republican 
challenger lynn martin republicans had high hopes for this one 
but simon proved stronger than they thought 
iowa republican gov terry branstad is holding off democratic 
challenger don avenson who had strong support from abortion rights 
groups iowans dont tend to reelect democratic senators but sen 
tom harkin has a strong chance to break that tradition gop rep 
tom tauke is within reach of an upset but has been unable to catch 
harkin in preelection surveys 
kansas gop gov mike hayden looked like a sure loser to 
democrat joan finney a month ago but her hard line against 
abortion appears to have hurt her and hayden had a narrow lead in 
the latest poll 
kentucky sen mitch mcconnell has led in all preelection 
polls over democrat harvey sloane but this is a strongly 
democratic state and sloane is given a chance for an upset 
maine former democratic gov joseph brennan wants his old job 
back and is challenging his republican successor john mckernan 
brennan held an early lead but the race now is a tossup 
massachusetts home of the voter rebellion outsider democrat 
john silber holds an uncertain lead over republican william weld in 
the race to succeed gov michael dukakis sen john kerry fighting 
to avoid being swept away by the rage that toppled incumbents in 
the september primary has opened a 20point lead over republican 
jim rappaport they were tied in surveys taken right after the 
primary 
michigan gov james blanchard is shaking off a challenge from 
republican john engler a new poll said engler was leading by 14 
points 
minnesota lake wobegon gone berserk democratic gov rudy 
perpich is viewed as potentially vulnerable to republican arne 
carlson who got onto the ballot only five days before election 
day carlson had lost the gop gubernatorial nomination to jon 
grunseth who was forced out of the race a week ago after 
allegations he swam nude with two teenage girls and cheated on two 
wives the fallout from the governors race is considered a factor 
in the surprising vulnerability of incumbent gop sen rudy 
boschwitz whos in a dead heat with democrat paul wellstone a new 
poll said boschwitz was pulling away 
nebraska gop gov kay orr once trailed democrat ben nelson but 
is now even up in the senate race democratic incumbent james exon 
appears to be pulling away from former rep hal daub 
new mexico former gov bruce king a democrat is leading 
republican frank bond but not by much 
north carolina one of the most watched races in the country is 
the senate battle between helms and his democratic challenger 
harvey gantt the black former mayor of charlotte gantt has been 
ahead in the polls but the contest has taken a nasty turn in the 
closing days 
ohio one of the best republican hopes for a gubernatorial 
pickup is this contest between republican george voinovich and 
democrat tony celebrezze to succeed democratic gov richard 
celeste the race has tightened in the past two weeks 
oklahoma democrat david walters leads republican bill price in 
the race to succeed gop gov henry bellmon 
oregon tight races for governor and senate democrat barbara 
roberts holds a narrow lead over republican dave frohnmayer in the 
race to succeed democratic gov neil goldschmidt in the senate 
race incumbent mark hatfield was caught by surprise and is in a 
tight race with democrat harry lonsdale 
rhode island the outlook is bleak for gop gov edward diprete 
who trails democrat bruce sundlun by 52 points in the senate race 
rep claudine schneiders challenge to democratic sen claiborne 
pell appears to have fallen short 
south dakota gop sen larry pressler leads democratic 
challenger ted muenster 
texas races dont get much nastier than this contest for 
governor between republican clayton williams and democrat ann 
richards williams once was far ahead but the race suddenly closed 
to a dead heat a week ago now richards is trying to exploit the 
disclosure that millionaire williams paid no income taxes in 1986 
vermont former gov richard snelling once looked like a 
landslide winner in his bid to get his old job back but democrat 
peter welch has moved within striking distance 
