in years past kremlinologists seeking clues to 
soviet politics scrutinized the lineup of leaders atop lenins 
mausoleum during the revolution day parade through red square 
during this wednesdays celebration of the communist holiday 
those wanting to know the political currents will look instead to 
the counterdemonstrations in moscows streets 
for the first time in the 73year history of the day marking the 
revolution that brought bolsheviks to power in russia alternative 
demonstrations have been officially sanctioned in the capital 
about 5000 people marched in an unofficial protest on 
revolution day last year this years alternative demonstration has 
the blessing of the moscow city council where radicals won seats 
last spring 
sundays editions of moskovskaya pravda the capitals communist 
party newspaper stated joyfully today we may firmly declare 
that the celebration of the anniversary will go on as usual 
the celebration will go on but it wont be a usual 
revolution day 
while the communist party puts on its grand show praising the 
1917 uprising and president mikhail s gorbachevs policies of 
perestroika protesters elsewhere in the city will be denouncing 
the coup engineered by vladimir lenin and mourning those killed 
during seven decades of repression 
demonstrators chose a symbolic route for their march starting 
at the communist partys central committee headquarters at the old 
square past a monument to stalins victims and ending at the 
house where the late human rights activist andrei sakharov lived 
our main slogan is from a totalitarian regime to democracy 
and humanism and we want to display this slogan to the whole 
world said lev shemayev of the moscow voters association which 
has organized anticommunist rallies this year 
in outlining the plans at a news conference last week he 
emphasized that one target of the protest would be gorbachev 
it is clear that everything stems from the walls of the old 
square where the president has his study he said referring to 
gorbachevs office as chief of the communist party 
another group of protesters led by radical deputies of the 
national and russian parliaments plan to march through red square 
carrying signs demanding the resignation of gorbachev defense 
minister dmitri yazov and others 
this march is scheduled to occur long after communist party 
supporters and military hardware have paraded over the cobblestones 
of red square gorbachev and the rest of the soviet leadership will 
have left their reviewing stand atop the mausoleum 
radical leaders such as moscow mayor gavriil popov and leningrad 
mayor anatoly sobchak initially urged that no festivities be held 
saying the communist system has been so destructive there is 
nothing to celebrate many of the 15 republics including the 
baltics voted to ban traditional parades 
gorbachev however ordered the parades to go on in major 
cities and the national parliament echoed his sentiments 
moskovskaya pravda has been printing letters from party members 
war veterans and others in support of celebrating the glorious 
date 
a group of moscow war veterans criticized those who would cancel 
the festivities saying the attempts to deprive the soviet people 
of their national holiday are blasphemous 
newspapers have reported on efforts to swell the ranks of the 
procommunist party parade with soviet army officers ordering 
soldiers to march in street clothes and militaryaffiliated 
schools compelling students to fall in step 
with the official parade still on some radicals felt that to do 
nothing would be a political mistake because it will play into 
the hands of the party and give the impression that all soviet 
people support the communists shemayev said 
not all the radicals agree 
popov said last week i am not going to march in any 
demonstrations although i will attend the official state 
ceremonies related to nov 7 
the national parliament had urged that alternative 
demonstrations not be held but opposition groups decided to defy 
the lawmakers and the city council approved 
lev ponomarov a radical deputy to the russian republics 
parliament sounded defensive friday in announcing protest plans 
it is not us who initiates these demonstrations we are 
forced to participate because we want to express a different 
viewpoint he said 
shemayev stressed that the national reconciliation of 
communists and noncommunists was another principal theme of the 
day 
we must emphasize the main philosophy that we are all now 
within the confines of the barbed wire of the soviet union he 
said and we are all countrymen whether we like or loathe each 
other 
