operatic repertory here hvorostovsky thrilled his audience with 
all the vocal power one could ask for and a range that carried up 
to the a above middle c 
there was some donizetti riccardos fiery aria from bellinis 
i puritani and finally two verdi showpieces millers aria 
from luisa miller and rodrigos dying o carlo ascolta from 
don carlo 
in this last number hvorostovskys purity of tone was 
astonishing as was his ability to sustain a long smooth line 
without apparently having to stop for breath like other human 
beings 
having roused the crowd to a fervor he outdid himself in a 
couple of encores the prologue scene from leoncavallos i 
pagliacci brought to mind the great leonard warren who made the 
part one of his specialties an aria from tchaikovskys queen of 
spades was heartrending in its beauty 
the excellent piano accompanist was mikhail arkadiev its no 
criticism of him to say one longed to hear the singer accompanied 
in the operatic selections by full orchestra 
hvorostovsky will be making his debut at several major opera 
houses around the world in the coming year la scala san 
francisco covent garden no plans have been announced yet to bring 
him to the metropolitan opera but the folks over at lincoln center 
can ill afford to let this talent elude them for long 
</TEXT>
