<TEXT>
fighting reportedly broke out in rwanda 
again after the government said it had driven back rebel forces 
that invaded from uganda 
meanwhile a french cabinet minister was scheduled to embark 
tuesday on a mission to revive a peace initiative in rwanda 
french officials said cooperation minister jacques pelletier 
would confer with several african heads of state including 
rwandas president juvenal habyarimana and president yoweri 
museveni of uganda 
france has deployed 300 paratroopers in rwanda to protect french 
civilians and diplomats and the airport in the event an evacuation 
was ordered several hundred french nationals already have left the 
central african country 
staterun rwanda radio said government troops blocked a rebel 
advance sunday after the insurgents penetrated three miles into 
rwanda from the gatuna and kaniga border posts 
ugandas official new vision newspaper said the rebels captured 
the border posts after heavy fighting saturday in which 35 
government soldiers were killed and eight others were captured 
new vision also reported that the rebels had attacked in several 
other areas in the last five days including the southeastern town 
of rusumu on rwandas border with tanzania and burundi 
the government on thursday said it had retaken five towns in the 
countrys northeast and driven the rebels back into uganda but 
rebel officer lodviko twahirwa told the newspaper other insurgents 
had hidden deep inside rwanda 
the rebels many of whom deserted ugandas army to join the 
invasion when it began last month accuse rwandas government of 
corruption and say they want to replace it with a democracy in 
which all ethnic groups could participate 
the rebel forces are drawn mainly from the hundreds of thousands 
of tutsis who fled rwanda in the late 1950s and early 1960s at 
that time the majority hutu gained control in a bloody power 
struggle in which more than 10000 tutsi were killed about 250000 
rwandan refugees live in uganda 
