<TEXT>
miners staged a twohour warning strike at 
virtually all polands deep coal mines today to demand pay 
increases and protest the effects of economic reform on the crucial 
industry 
the strike called by the solidarity miners union affected some 
70 hard coal mines only four of the countrys mines were not 
involved but workers at those expressed sympathy for the job 
action the official pap news agency said 
the protest was called after months of negotiations between the 
solidarityled government and the miners unions produced no 
agreement on pay raises industry ministry spokesman jan golab 
said 
the council of ministers led by prime minister tadeusz 
mazowiecki was to discuss the protest in the stateowned mining 
industry today golab said 
but he said the demand for pay twice the national average 
cannot be met for economic reasons by the impoverished 
government treasury workers nationwide earn an average 126 
monthly but miners earn 179 golab said 
the miners say their economic situation is worsening and that 
they were promised higher salaries during the 1989 negotiations 
between the thencommunist authorities and solidarityled 
opposition 
the growing unrest in the traditionally volatile industry comes 
three weeks before polands first popular presidential election 
mazowiecki faces solidarity chairman lech walesa in a contest 
focused on the governments economic reforms 
coal is a crucial export for poland and the main domestic energy 
source the mines mostly in the silesia region of southwestern 
poland were heavily subsidized by the government under the 
socialized system and miners received many fringe benefits 
including shops for goods in short supply 
postcommunist poland is stripping away subsidies forcing state 
industries to become selfsufficient as the country switches to a 
marketdriven capitalist economy 
but the mining industry is so economically unsound because of 
inefficiency decades of artificially low governmentset prices 
for coal and other factors that high levels of support from the 
national treasury continue to be required 
</TEXT>
