independence leader aung san she is a leader of the national 
league for democracy which easily won elections in may the 
military government has refused to yield power 
the award statement said that under burmas military rulers 
massacres extrajudicial executions detention torture and 
harassment has befallen thousands and thousands of peaceful 
civilians 
amnesty international and several western governments and groups 
have made similar charges against the government which came to 
power in september 1988 in a crackdown on the prodemocracy 
movement that left thousands dead 
