<TEXT>
charles stuarts lawyer does not have to testify 
to a grand jury about a conversation he had with his client the day 
before stuart leaped to his death from a bridge the state supreme 
court ruled today 
the court in a 41 ruling said john t dawleys attorneyclient 
privilege was not undone with his clients suicide on jan 4 that 
threw a final twist in the deeply mysterious plot to kill stuarts 
wife carol 
the mouth of the attorney shall be forever sealed the court 
wrote 
the privilege of insisting that the attorney keep confidential 
the clients disclosures made to the attorney in his or her 
professional capacity belongs only to the client and therefore can 
be waived only by the client the court said in a decision 
written by justice francis p oconnor 
the suffolk county district attorneys office had wanted dawley 
to testify before a grand jury gathering evidence in the death of 
carol stuart a tax attorney who was shot and killed oct 23 1989 
dawley met with stuart for about two hours on jan 3 and 
investigators contend that the 30yearold fur store manager 
admitted to his lawyer that he killed his wife 
the next day stuart jumped to his death off the tobin bridge 
into boston harbor 
officials at the district attorneys office were in conference 
this morning and could not immediately be reached for comment 
dawley declined to comment on the courts ruling until he 
received a copy 
id like to read it before i comment on that he said 
a grand jury has met periodically since attempting to piece 
together details of the crime no charges have been filed 
suffolk county assistant district attorney thomas mundy argued 
that the grand jury would be deprived of potentially relevant 
information if dawley did not testify 
paul leary first assistant district attorney said the grand 
jury which has made little progress in recent weeks has been 
waiting for the decision on dawley 
but attorneys representing the stuart family argued that the 
court would be setting a dangerous precedent by tampering with the 
attorneyclient privilege 
charles stuart originally told police he and his pregnant wife 
were attacked by a lone black gunman in their car after they left 
a birthing class the couples baby delivered prematurely after 
the shooting died 17 days later 
stuart shot in the stomach called police on his cellular phone 
and when he lost consciousness emergenc operators located him by 
listening for police car sirens heard over the phone 
the case intensified racial friction in boston after police 
stormed homes in a black neighborhood in search of mrs stuarts 
killer 
but stuart became the prime suspect after his brother matthew 
implicated him in the crime matthew stuart told authorities that 
under his brothers instructions he drove to the crime scene and 
retrieved several personal belongings of carol stuart plus a gun 
believed to be the murder weapon 
dorothy stuart stuarts mother and the executor of his estate 
has told the grand jury she couldnt waive her son attorneyclient 
privilege and she would not have done so if the law had allowed 
her 
the state had argued that stuart having died no longer can 
be harmed by the disclosure of his communications to his attorney 
and that the privilege should be overridden because of societys 
interest in finding who killed carol stuart and her son 
but the court disagreed with that contention saying that the 
clients and the publics interests are best served by a rule of 
confidentiality that applies both before and after the death of the 
client 
in his dissent justice joseph r nolan said that despite the 
courts ruling attorneyclient privilege is not absolute and the 
possibility that charles stuart did not kill his wife meant the 
killer could still be on the loose 
under the courts analysis there is no safety valve no 
mechanism by which the attorneyclient privilege may ever be 
overridden by the court in the interests of justice nolan wrote 
i would argue the court to adopt this very narrow interests of 
justice exception 
leo v boyle president of the massachusetts bar association 
said the attorney client privilege is of ancient origin and is 
at the heart of the delivery of justice once you bend the law for 
a single case no matter how tragic the legal framework of our 
society starts to crumble the court did the unpopular thing but 
undoubtedly the right thing 
