shortly after the aug 24 deadline set by the iraqis 
electricity and water to the compound were cut off the loss of air 
conditioning made the blistering heat almost unbearable and some 
people chose to sleep outdoors to avoid the stifling rooms in the 
ambassadors residence or offices that had been converted to 
sleeping quarters in the administration building 
there werent enough generators or fuel to keep the freezers 
running so the frozen food mostly turkey was eaten first there 
was plenty at first but it spoilednone too soon for some 
compound inmates tired of the steady turkey diet theyve since 
resorted to canned tuna supplemented by rice and fresh dates that 
grow on the compound 
with the water cut off they couldnt use toilets so they dug a 
trench at one side of the compound and use it as a latrine 
there were no showers but they continued to use the swimming 
pool as long as possible sources say it is stagnant now and the 
water unsuitable for most uses 
last week however secretary of state james a baker iii 
disclosed the embassy occupants had dug a well and struck water 
good enough for washing they even washed their cars just to show 
off for the guards and to water the vegetable garden theyve 
planted behind the ambassadors house they have yet to harvest any 
vegetables but are reported hopeful they will have a crop before 
the desert temperatures drop into the 30s in midwinter 
theyre very elated about their new well said margie 
howell wife of us ambassador nathaniel howell who was packing 
to come home when the invasion blocked his departure mrs howell 
who had left a short time before told the nbc today show last week 
she goes to the state department every day and speaks to her 
husband over a special satellite telephone link that keeps 
communications open between the embassy and washington 
the principal assignment of those who remain behind is to keep 
in contact with the 600 or so americans who are still in hiding in 
kuwait to avoid being rounded up and added to the ranks of the 
human shield saddam hussein has assembled to protect strategic 
installations from attack 
the loal phones still work but the state department says the 
iraqis tap the embassy phone lines to try to catch americans in 
hiding to keep conversation to a minimum and prevent the iraqis 
from tracing calls to peoples hideouts sources said the 
diplomats use voice of america radio broadcasts to signal citizens 
to call when there is news about evacuation flights medicine or 
emergencies and the embassy tries to maintain a team of 
wardens beyond the walls who serve as intermediaries between 
the diplomats and those in hiding 
when theyre not working the phones mrs howell said those 
inside the compound work out on exercise equipment left behind by 
the marine guards read and play cards 
actually this is our third war she told nbc we were in 
egypt in 67 and then we were in beirut in 75 when that war 
started 
