<TEXT>
officials in soviet georgia have decided to move 
wednesdays revolution day military parade from the streets of the 
republics capital of tbilisi to a field on an army base tass 
reported monday 
the decision in the southern republic where noncommunists have 
just scored a big electoral victory marked the latest blow to the 
oncesacred holiday and a further erosion of the communist partys 
role in society 
the holiday marks the anniversary of the 1917 bolshevik 
revolution 
at least two officially sanctioned counterdemonstrations by 
anticommunist groups are being held this year in moscow with the 
protesters urging a day of mourning for people killed by the 
totalitarian regime alternative rallies also will be held in 
leningrad kiev minsk and other cities 
also on monday the government newspaper izvestia printed on its 
front page a message by russian orthodox church patriarch alexi ii 
in which he called for a sober analysis of the holiday 
let this day be a day of neither celebrations nor damnations 
but a day of meditation from the depth of human conscience the 
patriarch wrote 
let all the years that passed since october 1917 rise in our 
conscience one after another and persuade us not to pay for 
politicians experiments and principles with human destinies he 
said 
officials of the transcaucasian military district in georgia 
will hold the march by soldiers and the display of tanks and other 
hardware on a parade ground of a tbilisi garrison unit the 
official soviet news agency said the traditional parade route is 
the central thoroughfare of the capital 
this step was prompted by the difficult sociopolitical 
situation in the republic and by our desire not to aggravate it 
said lt gen a skory a member of the district military council 
in parliamentary elections in georgia last month noncommunist 
parties scored victories on a platform of capitalism and 
independence from the soviet union 
