soldiers in the main square of ayacucho seriously injuring 17 
members of the armed forces and two civilians police said monday 
the government lifted the state of emergency oct 24 in 
ayacucho a departmental capital 230 miles southeast of lima and 
the birthplace of the shining path 
in the coastal city of trujillo 305 miles north of lima rebels 
sunday detonated a car bomb outside government health offices and 
