the murder trial of marlon brandos 
son was delayed indefinitely monday by an appeals court decision to 
review the status of brandos daughter who is recovering from a 
drug overdose in tahiti 
cheyenne brando 20 is the key witness to events that led to 
the shooting death of her 26yearold lover dag drollet at the 
actors home on may 16 brandos son christian 32 had been 
scheduled to go on trial monday for firstdegree murder 
miss brando fled to tahiti a month after the killing gave birth 
to drollets child and had refused to return to california to 
testify authorities in tahiti also have barred her exit charging 
her as an accomplice in drollets murder 
the legal tangle over her testimony led to a lastminute stay 
prosecutors say they cant win the case without her testimony 
the states 2nd district court of appeal issued a brief ruling 
late monday upholding the stay and ordering legal briefs to be 
submitted by brandos attorney on nov 13 with responding briefs 
from the prosecution on nov 19 
the trial is on hold said district attorney spokeswoman 
sandi gibbons 
the threemember appeals panel said it would decide the issues 
on the basis of written documents however the court left the door 
open for the lower court to reconsider its role in prosecution 
efforts to force miss brando to return from tahiti and testify 
the main dispute is whether a california court can issue an 
international letter seeking official help from french authorities 
to arrange miss brandos testimony 
judges in superior and federal courts have refused to rule 
saying they lacked jurisdiction in the international matter but 
the appeals court said the superior court could take up the 
question again 
on thursday night miss brando was rushed to a tahitian hospital 
in a coma by friday she awakened and was reported to be 
recovering from a drug overdose 
cheyennes troubled life has been a subplot to the brando affair 
from the start she is said to be emotionally disturbed addicted 
to drugs and still suffering effects of a nearfatal auto accident 
in 1989 
she was seven months pregnant when marlon brando dialed 911 to 
tell police there had been a shooting at his mansion 
prosecutors say christian brando decided to kill drollet because 
he had been physically abusing his sister 
defense attorney robert shapiro said christian brando and 
drollet fought over a gun that accidentally went off 
miss brandos version of events has never been clear she has 
given at least five depositions in the united states and tahiti 
but shapiro says they have contained conflicting accounts 
marlon brando who wept last month when he spoke of his 
daughters plight flew to tahiti friday to be with her he is 
expected to testify at the trial 
