president bush signed a 492 billion 
deficitreduction package into law monday night a reluctant 
electioneve reminder to voters of pending tax increases 
bush delayed signing the controversial budget package until 820 
pm 920 pm est beating a midnight est deadline when 
temporary spending authority was to expire the tortured passage 
last month of the package which includes 140 billion in tax 
increases as well as significant cuts in government spending 
plunged bushs administration into disarray and crippled his 
oncehigh approval ratings 
the president who spent the day campaigning on behalf of 
republican candidates in texas also signed the 13 appropriations 
bills that provide money for the government for the next 11 months 
bush wound up five days of political travel urging voters to 
get out there and vote ending a midterm election campaign 
marked by mixed messages and squabbling among his advisers 
the budget package caused the president considerable political 
damage within his own party and white house advisers had worked 
hard to move voters attention off the budget fiasco 
camaigning in his adoptive home state the president sought to 
emphasize positive electioneve themes acting on a recommendation 
from some advisers to look more presidential 
in the final days leading up to tuesdays midterm elections 
bush has been buffeted by conflicting recommendations from senior 
advisers about how to make the best of his falling popularity said 
aides who spoke on the condition of anonymity 
after bush found that the slumping economy and his wavering 
positions on tax and budget issues were not playing well to 
republican audiences he first embarked on a blistering attack on 
democrats blaming them for shoving new tax increases down his 
throat 
aides said that the democratbashing approach primarily urged 
by bushs combative chief of staff john sununu appeared to be 
backfiring 
according to sources bushs former pollster robert teeter and 
his 1988 media consultant roger ailes bypassed sununu last week 
and persuaded bush to lighten up and to stress positive themes 
one official said that bushs apparent wavering on themes over 
the past few days did not reflect shift of positions as much as 
conflicting advice 
as bushs political sights began to refocus toward his own 1992 
reelection effort the president also vented his frustration at 
commentaries on his diminished popularity and the mood of the 
electorate 
at a gop rally in tyler bush lashed out at the cynics these 
washington pundits that we see on these tiring shows all the 
time 
i dont know if youre like me maybe youve enjoyed these 
things but i can only take so much selfflagellation bush 
declared 
dont tell me whats wrong with this country show us whats 
right about it he asserted with gop gubernatorial candidate 
clayton williams at his side 
at a rally in waco bush raised the spectre of former president 
jimmy carter saying i get so tired of contentions that 
theres a great malaise about the political process 
bush also continued his barrage against saddam hussein 
demanding the iraqi leader withdraw from kuwait 
unchecked and uncontrolled aggression could be world war 
tomorrow he said 
at a final campaign gala in houston the presence of three or 
four protesters shouting no war for oil gave bush an entry into 
one of his favorite lines that the us military buildup in saudi 
arabia is not to secure oil but to oppose naked aggression 
the protesters were hustled out of the room 
bush was to vote in houston on tuesday before returning to 
washington 
as bush and his wife barbara campaigned across texas the 
massachusettsborn and connecticutraised president boasted of 
their longtime ties to the state 
i am a texan and i am proud of it and i know texas quality 
when i see it bush told his tyler audience he noted he had 
voted in texas in every election since 1948 
by any account bushs participation in the midterm elections 
has been remarkable attending 115 political fund raisers and 
rallies as president and raising nearly 90 million for republicans 
over the last year and a half 
what would it take for bush to declare a victory for 
republicans i expect hell claim victory no matter what 
happens white house spokesman marlin fitzwater said 
