<TEXT>
president bush officially ended months of 
partisan brawling with congress over taxes and the budget monday by 
signing a bill to cut 492 billion from the deficit over the next 
five years 
no one got everything he or she wanted but the end product is 
a compromise that merits enactment bush said in a statement 
affixed to the largest package of deficit cuts and tax increaeses 
in history 
bush also signed 13 separate appropriations bills to finance the 
government through the fiscal year that began last oct 1 and to 
carry out the edicts of the budget compromise 
while bush convened a rose garden ceremony to unveil an earlier 
version of the package he signed the final measure in private 
just hours before the midnight deadline after dinner at a local 
restaurant 
eleven of the bills were flown from washington by special 
courier so bush could sign them all together 
the plan calls for over 140 billion in new taxes over the next 
five years including in increase in the tax rate on the richest 
americans from the current 28 percent to 31 percent and even a few 
points higher for some 
bushs abandonment of his no new taxes pledge and the long 
budget stalemate between the white house and the 
democraticcontrolled congress contributed to bushs preelection 
decline in popularity 
it also caused severe dissension within the ranks of his own 
party as many republicans repudiated the package and bushs 
turnabout on taxes 
this act is the result of long hard work by the 
administration and the congress bush said in the statement 
he called the measure an important measure for ensuring 
americas longterm economic growth 
bush said that the package embodied a new fiscal order for the 
federal government 
the measure will lower taxes to 31 percent for some 35 
million uppermiddleincome taxpayers who now pay a 33 percent rate 
under an anonomaly in the tax code that has placed their marginal 
rates at more than the top rate for those earning substantially 
more 
the budget deal also phases out deductions for highincome 
americans and imposes higher taxes on gasoline cigarettes 
alcohol and on luxury items like exotic cars and yachts 
the legislation includes a new 22 billion program of tax 
credits and grant money for child care mostly for poor working 
families 
the president said the child care measure will enlarge the 
opportunities of parents to obtain the child care they desire 
bush also signed 13 separate bills providing funds for fiscal 
1991 for all federal agencies and programs among them 
a 153 billion foreign aid bill that would forgive egypts 
past military debt and sharply restrict aid to el salvador 
a 182 billion bill for health and human service programs that 
provides money for new programs to combat aids while retaining a 
10year limitation on the use of federal money for abortions 
a 193 billion measure to operate the commerce justice and 
state departments including more money for savings and loan 
prosecutions 
a 268 billion defense spending bill that cuts 2 billion from 
the presidents 47 billion request for the strategic defense 
initiative while keeping alive the stealth bomber sought by the 
administration and the tiltrotor v22 osprey assault transport 
bush has tried for two years to kill 
</TEXT>
