information following the oct 17 earthquake that devastated parts 
of northern california 
the washington daily news led those in the under50000 
circulation class for uncovering the fact that city officials for 
eight years had known cancercausing chemicals were in the local 
tap water the disclosure resulted in a twomonth water ban an 
improved treatment system and state and federal reviews of water 
regulations 
