when americans prepare to vote today they might 
dwell again on those spending cuts passed by congress that will 
somehow cut household budgets but raise uncle sams expenditures 
a lot of americans say it doesnt make sense and it probably 
doesnt at the least its confusing did congress cut spending as 
it says it did or did it merely cut the spending ability of 
american households 
the easy explanation is the one usually offered that because of 
the seriousness of the budget deficit an enlightened congress 
reached the tortuously difficult decision simultaneously to raise 
your taxes and cut its spending 
but there is more to the explanation than that and some critics 
contend it involves financial sleight of hand accounting gimmicks 
