author edward rice was 13 when he first 
encountered sir richard francis burton in the english explorers 
book wanderings in three countries 
later supporting himself as a freelance photographer for the 
united nations the world health organization and town and country 
magazine rice spent about three years in india traveled overland 
1800 miles up the indus valley in pakistan and went to kenya and 
somalia which burton opened up to the west 
whenever i traveled burton was always there because i turned 
to burton as a reference says the 72yearold rice whose 
captain sir richard francis burton the secret agent who made the 
pilgrimage to mecca discovered the kama sutra and brought the 
arabian nights to the west is a surprise best seller 
just coincidentally i was going to the same places that 
burton went coincidentally well i dont know maybe burtons 
spirit was up there telling me you go here or there he says 
and laughs squinting through pale blue eyes under a shock of white 
hair 
rices health has plagued him however like burton the author 
has persevered through near blindness and more 
he signed a contract for the biography in 1979 by 1980 his 
eyes were failing by 1985 he was legally blind soon thereafter 
he underwent open heart surgery he has had two eye operations 
when he finally finished the book in 1987 his publishing house 
was being overhauled and his editor left he took the book to 
charles scribners sons which published it 
rice may be one of the last burton biographers who saw cities 
the way burton did i was there just before westernization 
