<TEXT>
in taking on the presidency of the american 
red cross elizabeth dole is moving to the helm of an organization 
that has known controversy from the days of clara barton to the era 
of aids and the loma prieta earthquake 
she isnt likely to face criticism for living in a tent and 
directing operations from the field as red cross founder barton 
did but she could end up having easily as many battles on her hand 
as she did in president bushs cabinet 
after a year in which it faced record disaster expenditures the 
organization has taken heat not only for its handling of such 
emergencies but for its role as a supplier of blood for 
