columbia sc ap james dickey can trace his long rise to 
the heights of american letters to a single word in a single line 
of a forgotten sonnet by an obscure poet 
he recalled the occasion recently during a poetry class at the 
university of south carolina 
i was a young air force pilot in okinawa during world war ii 
i was sitting by the bay overlooking a graveyard where thousands of 
americans were buried and there were no flowers 
i had with me an anthology of poems one of them was by joseph 
trumbull stickney who had died when he was 30 just when he was 
getting going it contained this line about the pagan god apollo 
and all his island shivered into flowers 
i thought that was truly unusual truly remarkable shivered 
into flowers shivered 
i thought maybe i could do something like that maybe maybe 
i decided to try 
