<TEXT>
lee lamented at the time that his country was the smallest of 
shrimps in a sea of hungry fish 
few states faced sovereignty in such dismal circumstances 
unemployment poverty and ethnic tensions were rife the economy 
was weak and the armed forces ineffective indonesia was 
threatening military action against malaysia and singapore 
i say without the slightest remorse that we wouldnt be here 
we would have not made economic progress if we had not intervened 
on very personal matters who your neighbor is how you live the 
noise you make how you spit or what language you use lee once 
said in a speech 
more than half of the present citizens were born during lees 
tenure and more than 80 percent have known no other leader during 
their adult lives 
his assorted views and prejudices on matters ranging from good 
neighborliness to genetics have over the years assumed the force 
of law some are resented as quirky or intrusive but are not 
seriously challenged 
those who challenged lees leadership found themselves subject 
to arrest detention without trial public humiliation and general 
harassment by a government reluctant to acknowledge dissent 
he has survived in confrontational politics to the point that he 
is respected and regarded with awe but not love that appears to 
be the image he prefers in much the way of an emperor in imperial 
china 
in answering foreigners who criticize his tough treatment of 
opponents lee once told an interviewer that the chinese people 
have no concept of a loyal opposition their support is firm even 
if you detain people without trial but once that support is 
withdrawn it is sudden and complete lee said 
if you break faith with them and lose your mandate youve had 
it it will go completely the other way 
an island about the size of chicago singapore has no natural 
resources except a strategic location and the skills of a 
multiracial population 
lee demanded discipline to overcome hardships obedience hard 
work cleanliness thrift and the profit motive all played a part 
as a shabby colonial backwater was transformed 
years of firm political leadership and stable economic growth 
helped attract investment by multinational corporations seeking a 
doorway to the booming markets of the asiapacific region now its 
a thriving financial and manufacturing center with hightech 
industries firstclass schools and glitzy shopping centers 
the lee administration has a reputation for honesty efficiency 
and a strong sense of direction standards are high and there is a 
strict moral code 
do not try to get a government on the cheap money politics 
will result in a poor bunch of mps members of parliament plus a 
lot of hypocrisy fiddling and eventually dishonesty and 
corruption lee told the country on aug 8 in his final national 
day address as prime minister 
tipping jaywalking littering and discourtesy are officially 
denounced those who neglect to flush public toilets after use may 
be fined 
those suspected of more serious transgressions such as 
subversion and drug abuse can expect no mercy suspected 
subversives can be detained indefinitely under the internal 
security act without being charged or put on trial dozens of 
convicted drug traffickers have been hanged 
lee has described his role in recent years as that of 
chairman of a citystate run on corporate lines cabinet 
ministers act as executive directors largely untroubled by 
ideological issues or domestic political infighting they are 
chosen less for their appeal among voters than their capacity to 
manage a department effectively 
the danger now is that many believe that wehave arrived and 
can therefore relax in that case standards will go down and we 
will lose out as long as we do not forget this we need not fear 
the future lee said 
