<TEXT>
carl reiner was in an especially jovial mood the 
other day during one leg of a daunting nationwide promotion tour 
for his new film sibling rivalry that would have tired a man 
half his age 
but reiner tall trim and as busy as ever at 68 still looks a 
lot like his most wellknown character alan brady the arrogant 
variety show host on the old dick van dyke show 
his good humor was evident despite decidedly mixed reviews about 
the movie his latest film in a career that spans 40 years and 
includes such tv and movie comedy classics as your show of 
shows wheres poppa all of me and the jerk reiner 
directed sibling rivalry 
the critics have not been not especially kind to the comedy 
which stars kirstie alley and involves a man who died during sex 
with her and the various cases of mistaken identity that occur as a 
result 
the title refers to three sets of siblings in the film and how 
they interact and compete with with each other familial rivalry is 
a familiar subject to reiner both with his own brother who he 
credits with pushing him into show business and his famous son 
rob 
the prospect of a new reiner comedy is a lipsmacking one rob 
reiner that is not papa carl whose best comedies were made years 
ago wrote the new york post film critic in panning sibling 
rivalry 
carl reiner does not dispute those sentiments 
rob had the toughest time of all my kids he said he 
wanted to be in show business and he had a father who was going on 
all cylinders he was in competition with me and he was impatient 
then he ended up outrunning dad 
reiner lists his sons movies with pride saying hes been up 
at bat six times and you cant find anything really wrong with his 
work 
reiner also said that his son outstripped me as far as acting 
too whenever theyd see us on the street theyd start yelling 
hey meathead one time somebody called him meatloaf and i yelled 
back no its meathead 
according to carl reiner family members have always been 
competitive with each other but theyve also remained loyal 
reiners brother charlie who owns a printing business in 
atlanta was always the funnier one when they were growing up 
in the bronx the sons of a watchmaker 
but charlie suffered because i was the more quiet studious 
one and my mother would always say why cant you be more like 
your brother carl we still talk about it 
but it was his brother who urged him to enroll in drama school 
and become an actor and his brother still religiously tapes all 
reiners appearances on tv and saves all news clippings about him 
everytime im on carson he still tapes it said reiner 
reiners other two children are daughter annie a playwright 
and artist and lucas who directed the film spirit of 76 
my other kids have had a problem with it said reiner of 
both his success and robs annie was showing some of her work 
recently and the first people who greeted her at the door said 
arent you carl reiners daughter shes trying to have to her 
own identity you want to make it on your own 
but reiner said his family is very closeknit despite the 
inherent rivalries and often gather for dinners at the beverly 
hills home he shares with wife of 47 years 
estelle reiner played the woman in the deli in rob reiners 
film when harry met sally who said ill have whatever 
shes having in the memorable scene in which meg ryan faked an 
orgasm 
the reiner family has a history of inserting relatives and other 
autobiographical details into their work carl reiners most 
celebrated comedy the dick van dyke show was set in new 
rochelle ny where he lived with his wife after their marriage 
and van dyke character was of course named rob after you know 
who 
but even if he believes rob has surpassed him as a director 
carl reiner is keeping as busy as ever he continually sifts 
through new scripts in search of a new movie to direct he was 
eager to return to beverly hills where hes in the midst of a 
novel about hollywood 
im a worker he said ive worked steadily all my life 
ive become venerable ive gone through several incarnations but 
ive kept current theres a whole generation of adults who grew up 
with me 
he and his wife live there yearround with the exception of six 
weeks they spend in the south of france each year reiners best 
friend is mel brooks with whom he wrote the legendary 2000 
yearold man they have dinner together several times a week and 
go out to movies 
</TEXT>
