<TEXT>
these tips for protecting your credit cards during the holiday 
shopping season come from control data corps telemoney services 
beware of pickpockets especially when amid holiday crowds 
carry only the cards you plan to use 
tear up and dispose of receipt carbons 
do not give your credit card number over the phone unless you 
dialed the number 
save your receipts and compare them with your monthly bills to 
verify purchases and amounts if theres a disagreement write to 
your card issuer 
keep a personallog of credit card numbers and card 
cancellation information keep it separate from the cards 
do not let a merchant copy your credit card number on your 
personal check 
do not tell anyone your personal identification number do not 
keep the number with your cards 
sign each new credit card when you get it cut up and throw 
