<TEXT>
ball corps failure to obtain financing for 
a 1025 billion acquisition of a european can producer illustrates 
how important or fatal timing can be to expansion plans 
a year ago experts say the munciebased manufacturer of 
containers and aerospace systems would have had no problem finding 
625 million in cash to pay peter kiewet sons inc for the 
european operations of continental can co 
kiewet of omaha neb also would have received 400 million in 
ball stock 
however in the three months since the tentative deal was 
announced world financial markets have been thrown into turmoil 
amid the persian gulf crisis 
the prospect of a recession has loomed larger the magnitude of 
the savingsandloan crisis has become more clear and banks have 
felt the pinch of regulatory oversight 
its all coming to the front here simultaneously said 
robert c klemkosky a financial market expert at the indiana 
university school of business in 1989 this deal would have 
gone it would have been a slam dunk 
wall street agrees 
i think it has less to do with ball than it has to do with the 
credit markets today said robert bishop a stock analyst with 
salomon brothers inc 
its more difficult to get financing today than it was back in 
july youre in a situation where you have a big sampl bailout going 
on were starting to find out more about all the loans that were 
made throughout the 80s bishop said 
he added the gulf certainly didnt help matters any 
ball announced the acquisition plans on july 30 three days 
before iraq invaded kuwait at the time ball stock was trading 
around 32 per share and the dow jones industrial average was 
threatening to break 3000 today ball trades closer to 26 
reflecting the stock markets loss of about 16 percent during the 
three months of the usled military buildup in the gulf 
ball and kiewet announced oct 26 their deal was off 
unfortunately due in major part to the recent turmoil in 
world financial markets and in particular the us banking 
community ball has not yet arranged financing and the certainty 
of closing the transaction on the agreed upon terms and time frame 
have become compromised they said in a joint statement 
ball officials have declined to comment further on the 
circumstances that led to the deals failure 
they stood to gain much from acquiring continental caneurope 
ball already was established as one of the top five producers of 
beer and soft drink cans in the united states but lacked a major 
presence in one of the worlds fastest growing markets europe 
ball has only a plastics plant in northern ireland and an 
electronics operation in germany 
continental can europes no 3 container producer appeared to 
provide the opportunity ball long had sought but never attained 
ball has abandoned european joint ventures that never proved as 
profitable as hoped and it failed two years ago to acquire 
metalbox ltd a continental can competitor eventually bought by a 
french suitor 
packaging revenues would have tripled continental can had sales 
of 147 billion last year and projected them to reach 166 
billion in 1990 ball container sales last year were only about 
half of that 781 million 
ball which likes to keep its debttoequity ratio around 40 
percent was prepared to temporarily sacrifice that conservative 
position financing would have raised the ratio to 60 percent 
qualifying the deal as a highly leveraged transaction 
such deals attract closer scrutiny and that no doubt scared 
some lenders 
the markets going to look very skeptically at that 
klemkosky said the banks are selfimposing capital rationing 
banks are just being extremely careful who theyre lending to 
h edward schollmeyer an analyst with painewebber inc 
speculated ball may have been forced eventually to walk away from 
financing that came at too high a price in interest and bank fees 
no matter how badly it wanted continental can 
they spent a lot of money working on it and i think theres a 
lot of broken hearts schollmeyer said 
