soybean futures settled 3 cents to 12 cents lower with the 
contract for delivery in november at 581 a bushel the lowest 
settlement for nearterm soybeans since aug 2 
analysts traced the steep midday selloff to two main factors 
fading hopes for sales of soybean meal to the soviet union and 
expectations that thursdays agriculture department crop report 
will contain a significantly larger soybean harvest projection than 
last months government estimate of 182 billion bushels 
